1 (3) The department shall certify a person as a state-certified doula if the person pays the fees
2 prescribed by the department and:
3 (a) submits a completed application as required by the department;
4 (b) satisfactorily completes competencies that meet the requirements established by the
5 department by rule;
6 (c) has not engaged in unprofessional conduct as defined in 37-1-410; and
7 (d) is not currently subject to any disciplinary proceedings.
8 (4) The department shall coordinate with doulas to establish certification requirements and oversee
9 the certification of state-certified doulas.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Voluntary certification -- practice as doula without certification
12 permitted. Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] prohibits a person from practicing as a doula without obtaining
13 certification under [section 2].
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Rulemaking. The department shall adopt rules necessary to carry out
16 the provisions of [sections 1 through 4].
